content:
Below is a JavaScript code that will prompt users to input their names and messages, scramble them according to the provided character mapping, and display them on the HTML page. The user will see the scrambled messages on the page.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Scrambled Conversation</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Scrambled Conversation</h1>
    <button onclick="scrambleConversation()">Start Conversation</button>
    <div id="scrambledMessages"></div>

    <script>
        const scrambleMap = {
            'A': 'E', 'B': 'Q', 'C': 'X', 'D': 'Z', 'E': 'F',
            'F': 'Y', 'G': 'H', 'H': 'P', 'I': 'K', 'J': 'L',
            'K': 'W', 'L': 'M', 'M': 'S', 'N': 'O', 'O': 'T',
            'P': 'U', 'Q': 'R', 'R': 'D', 'S': 'N', 'T': 'V',
            'U': 'G', 'V': 'J', 'W': 'A', 'X': 'I', 'Y': 'B',
            'Z': 'C'
        };

        function scrambleText(text) {
            return text.toUpperCase().split('').map(char => {
                return scrambleMap[char] || char;
            }).join('');
        }

        function scrambleConversation() {
            const name = prompt("Enter your name:");
            const message = prompt("Enter your message:");

            if (name && message) {
                const scrambledName = scrambleText(name);
                const scrambledMessage = scrambleText(message);

                const displayElement = document.getElementById('scrambledMessages');
                displayElement.innerHTML += `<p><strong>${scrambledName}:</strong> ${scrambledMessage}</p>`;
            } else {
                alert("Please enter both your name and message.");
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

- **HTML Structure**: This consists of a button to start the conversation and a `div` to display the scrambled messages.
- **JavaScript Logic**:
  - A mapping object `scrambleMap` is created to map each character to its scrambled equivalent.
  - The `scrambleText` function converts the input text to uppercase, splits it into characters, maps each character using the `scrambleMap`, and joins them back into a scrambled string.
  - The `scrambleConversation` function prompts the user for their name and message, scrambles both using `scrambleText`, and then displays them in the `scrambledMessages` div.

This code provides a simple interface for scrambling messages according to the specified character mapping.
